        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="113" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Another way to rotate an object by using a geometric path is to use a                      <ph id="ph1">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.MatrixAnimationUsingPath&gt;</ph> object and set its                      <ph id="ph2">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.MatrixAnimationUsingPath.DoesRotateWithTangent%2A&gt;</ph> property to                      <ph id="ph3">`true`</ph>.</source>
        </trans-unit>
